#include 


int main(int argc,char *argv[])
{
    printf("Before fork...\n");
    if(fork() == 0)
    {
        printf("Hello World!\n");
        exit(0);
    }
    printf("After fork..\n");
    return 0;
}

We expect the output to be:
Before fork...
Hello World!
After fork...
However,  the actual output may become
Before fork...
After fork...
Hello World!
We would like to suspend the parent and let the child finish execution.

